HEADWORD: Pluviography
<hw>Plu`vi*og"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pluvia</ets> rain + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The branch of
meteorology treating of the automatic registration of the precipitation
of rain, snow, etc.; also, the graphic presentation of precipitation
data.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluviometer</ent>⟦br⟧
